---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="resume -- alexander campos" description="Operations engineer, intelligence systems builder. Capital One, Apple FCU, Guardian, ForgeFrame.">
  <article class="resume">
    <h1>Resume</h1>

    <section class="summary">
      <p>
        Operations and process engineering in regulated finance.
        Building local intelligence infrastructure on the side.
      </p>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <section>
      <h2>Technical Skills</h2>

      <h3>Intelligence Systems & Architecture</h3>
      <p class="skills">
        Multi-Provider LLM Routing (Anthropic/OpenAI/Ollama), Intent-Based Model Selection,
        Prompt Engineering (Chain-of-Thought, Structured Extraction), Retrieval-Augmented Context
        Injection, Hierarchical Memory Compression, MCP Protocol, Reframe Detection,
        Post-Session Intelligence Pipelines
      </p>

      <h3>Application Engineering</h3>
      <p class="skills">
        TypeScript, Node.js, React, Electron, SQLite/FTS5, Python, Astro,
        Web Workers, WebGL2/GLSL, Three.js, Web Audio API, Tone.js, HTML/CSS
      </p>

      <h3>Process & Operations Engineering</h3>
      <p class="skills">
        Pipeline Anomaly Detection, Process Modernization, Root-Cause Analysis,
        Dependency Sequencing, Rollback Architecture
      </p>

      <h3>Data & Observability</h3>
      <p class="skills">
        SQL (Advanced -- Postgres, Snowflake), Splunk (Search & Reporting),
        Real-Time Monitoring Dashboards, AWS, Looker Studio, QuickSight, Power BI
      </p>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <section>
      <h2>Experience</h2>

      <div class="role">
        <div class="role-header">
          <h3>Capital One -- Senior Process Manager, Card Legal Recoveries Operations</h3>
          <span class="dates">2025 -- Present | Richmond, VA</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Built process health monitoring for a $600M+ file exchange network.</strong>
            300+ daily regulatory transmissions had no unified failure tracking.
            Built a pipeline-backed anomaly detection system with predictive validation.
            Reduced manual monitoring effort by 78%.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Resolved a 20,000+ account logic failure.</strong> Data team was backlogged
            6+ weeks. Built SQL framework to isolate root cause, remediate impacted accounts,
            and document failure taxonomy. Process team now owns root-cause analysis.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Validated specifications for the $35B+ Discover merger integration.</strong>
            Owned technical validation of the Systems Integration Guide for legacy firm
            onboarding. Surfaced design-layer gaps in regulatory file exchange formats
            with Engineering and vendor partners. Zero transmission errors through cutover.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Designed a 5-month modernization roadmap for fragmented manual workflows.</strong>
            Staged automation with dependency sequencing, stakeholder gates, and rollback
            protocols. Learned Splunk, Postgres, and JSON parsing to unblock 6 months of
            stalled monitoring work.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="role">
        <div class="role-header">
          <h3>Apple Federal Credit Union -- Branch Operations Administrator</h3>
          <span class="dates">January 2020 -- 2025 | Fairfax, VA</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Promoted four times in five years</strong> -- from teller through loan
            underwriting and account management, to full branch operational strategy, then
            enterprise-level operational support across a 25-branch network during a major merger.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Completed B.S. at George Mason University concurrently</strong> while
            carrying a full-time operational role across all four promotion stages.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Built compliance tracking and reporting dashboards</strong> (Power BI) for
            regulatory documentation (NCUA, CFPB). Designed monitoring infrastructure and
            workflow automation that reduced complaint response cycles by 50%.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Proposed branch-wide modernization roadmap</strong> with VP and SVP backing.
            Designed automation strategy for manual workflows across the branch network.
            Approved and moved into implementation.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <section>
      <h2>Projects</h2>

      <div class="role">
        <div class="role-header">
          <h3>Guardian -- Desktop Intelligence Workspace</h3>
          <span class="dates">2023 -- Present</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          Open-source desktop application (Electron + React + Node.js) integrating
          chat, terminal, notes, and persistent memory into a single local-first interface.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Built a reframe detection engine</strong> that classifies when language models
            subtly rewrite user statements. Triggers automatic prompt correction when user-rated
            inaccuracy exceeds 40%.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Designed provider-agnostic model routing</strong> across Anthropic, OpenAI,
            and Ollama. Auto-selects by intent complexity and cost. Runs air-gapped on local
            models or through cloud APIs.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Designed hierarchical memory compression</strong> -- raw to summary to pattern
            to principle. Strength decay with retrieval reinforcement for long-term context
            retention.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Built post-session extraction pipeline.</strong> Extracts decisions, tasks,
            and code artifacts on conversation end. Generates typed notes and indexes into
            FTS5 for search.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="role">
        <div class="role-header">
          <h3>ForgeFrame -- Local Intelligence Infrastructure</h3>
          <span class="dates">2025 -- Present</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          Open-source local infrastructure for memory, routing, and provenance.
          Monorepo architecture -- MIT-licensed memory primitive, AGPL core.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Built the MCP Memory Server</strong> (MIT). SQLite-backed persistent memory
            implementing the Model Context Protocol. Strength decay, retrieval reinforcement,
            and semantic search.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Designed dual integration architecture</strong> -- MCP for ecosystem
            compatibility plus a localhost proxy for conversation intercept and PII scrubbing.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="role">
        <div class="role-header">
          <h3>acampos.dev -- This Site</h3>
          <span class="dates">2026</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          Hand-built with Astro and vanilla JS. WebGL2 ASCII shader over a Gray-Scott
          reaction-diffusion field in a Web Worker. Audio-reactive via Web Audio API.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <section>
      <h2>Education</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>M.Eng. Product Innovation</strong> -- In Progress
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>B.S. Business Administration, Management and Operations</strong> -- George Mason
        University, December 2024.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>

  <script is:inline>
    console.log(
      '%c you are reading the resume of someone who builds systems like this one. ',
      'color: #5BF29B; font-family: monospace; font-size: 11px;'
    );
  </script>
</Page>

<style>
  .resume {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .skills {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--white-60);
  }

  .role {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .role-header {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .role-header h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }

  .dates {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--white-45);
  }

  .role ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .role li {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .role li strong {
    color: var(--glow-hot);
  }
</style>
